  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Vanishing Stripes: Save the Bengal Tiger</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">100,000 tigers walked India&apos;s wild forests just a century ago and today, we are left with a mere 3200 individuals. Our country, is home to about 70% of the world&apos;s Bengal tiger population, where they unfortunately face an uncertain fate. Issues like poaching, habitat loss, human-tiger conflict, illegal trade control amongst others act as a significant threat to tigers. What can secure their future are conservation efforts that have yielded encouraging results; yet there is a need to do far more.</narrative>
  </description>
